    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">When to Replace Your Calculator with Custom Software</h2>
    <p>
      There comes a point where the effort of maintenance exceeds the benefit of the tool.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Signal 1: You Spend 20+ Hours a Week on Bids</h3>
    <p>
      If you are an owner-operator spending your evenings and weekends fighting with spreadsheets, you have reached a ceiling. This time leak prevents you from finding new leads or managing active sites.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Signal 2: Profit Leakage Between Quote and Completion</h3>
    <p>
      If your project "looks" profitable at the start but ends with a smaller margin than expected, your estimating tool is failing to capture reality. This drift is usually caused by missed line items or outdated pricing.
    </p>

    <figure class="my-10">
